        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 4:33PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 433 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles southeast of U L Bend Rec Area, or 32 miles west of Jordan,
moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brusett and U L Bend Rec Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
northeastern Montana.</instruction>
